results.name: Numbers m that divide 6^m + 5.
comment: Conjecture: For k > 1, k^m == 1 - k (mod m) has infinitely many positive solutions.
program: (MAGMA) [1] cat [n: n in [1..10^8] | Modexp(6, n, n) + 5 eq n];
xref: Solutions to k^m == k-1 (mod m): A006521 (k = 2), A015973 (k = 3), A327840 (k = 4), A123047 (k = 5), this sequence (k = 6).
results.author: _Juri-Stepan Gerasimov_, Sep 30 2019
